node.title: Victorian Opposition Leader tells Liberal MP caught drink driving not to contest next election
node.alt: Tim Smith looks thoughtful as he stands outdoors in parkland under a sunny blue sky.
node.description: Victorian Liberal leader Matthew Guy tells backbencher Tim Smith he should not contest his electorate of Kew next year, after Mr SmithÂ crashed his car while more than twice over the legal blood-alcohol limit.
node.content: ["Victorian Liberal leader Matthew Guy has told backbencher Tim Smith he should not contest his electorate of Kew next year, after Mr Smith\u00a0crashed his car while more than twice over the legal blood-alcohol limit.", "On Sunday, Mr\u00a0Smith resigned from the shadow cabinet and apologised for failing a blood alcohol test, calling it a\u00a0\"serious error of judgement\".", "Mr Guy said he met with Mr Smith on Monday and \"made it very clear to Tim that he wouldn't find his way onto the frontbench of any parliamentary Liberal Party that I lead\".", "\"And I made it clear that I didn't want him to nominate at the next election and that I didn't believe he should nominate for the seat of Kew,\" he said.", "\"Tim has and will reflect on my advice to him, he will then make a statement in his own time, I hope sooner rather than later.\"", "More to come."]
